headline: SYSCO TEAMSTERS IN CALIFORNIA AUTHORIZE STRIKE
summary: More than 400 Teamsters at Sysco San Francisco have voted unanimously to authorize a strike if the company refuses to deliver a fair contract. Drivers and warehouse workers are demanding wage increases, benefits, and working conditions that match or exceed standards already set by Teamsters at other food service providers in the Bay Area.
